"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T13:41:00.000Z","msg":"MSG乜乜乜<img src=\"/assets/faces/dogxm/wet.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dogxm/wet.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dogxm/wet.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T21:20:18.000Z","msg":"MSG is the king of flavor<img src=\"/assets/faces/xm/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"027e1723029fd872c46451e843e77d5e27f1e355","tid":2348052,"uid":38121,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T22:09:19.000Z","msg":"MSG is considered safe by the FDA but has been blamed for headaches, flushing and difficulty breathing. <br />\n<br />\nContrary to popular belief, decades of research fails to support the link between MSG and these reported side effects.<br />\n<br />\nNo adverse symptoms were observed when people consumed MSG as part of a meal-even at high doses (up to 147 grams/day), according to a review of studies, published in 2000 in the Journal of Nutrition.<br />\n<br />\nThere's one caveat though: eating large doses of MSG may lead to classic symptoms of Chinese Restaurant Syndrome when it is consumed solo and on an empty stomach.<br />\n<br />\nIn a 2013 study, researchers gave healthy adults about 10 grams of MSG on average (a fairly large dose) without any food. Almost all of them experienced headaches, as well as short-term increases in blood pressure and heart rate.<br />\n<br />\n簡單啲講，喺食物加入少量應該係完全冇害<br />\n如果空肚就咁食大量味精 (~10g) 就會有Chinese Restaurant Syndrome，即係頭痛出汗，皮膚發紅，呼吸困難咁。"},{"pid":"9980894634e19fecfd65eb119f19c94fbce29af4","tid":2348052,"uid":201036,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"quote":{"pid":"027e1723029fd872c46451e843e77d5e27f1e355","tid":2348052,"uid":38121,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T22:09:19.000Z","msg":"MSG is considered safe by the FDA but has been blamed for headaches, flushing and difficulty breathing. <br />\n<br />\nContrary to popular belief, decades of research fails to support the link between MSG and these reported side effects.<br />\n<br />\nNo adverse symptoms were observed when people consumed MSG as part of a meal-even at high doses (up to 147 grams/day), according to a review of studies, published in 2000 in the Journal of Nutrition.<br />\n<br />\nThere's one caveat though: eating large doses of MSG may lead to classic symptoms of Chinese Restaurant Syndrome when it is consumed solo and on an empty stomach.<br />\n<br />\nIn a 2013 study, researchers gave healthy adults about 10 grams of MSG on average (a fairly large dose) without any food. Almost all of them experienced headaches, as well as short-term increases in blood pressure and heart rate.<br />\n<br />\n簡單啲講，喺食物加入少量應該係完全冇害<br />\n如果空肚就咁食大量味精 (~10g) 就會有Chinese Restaurant Syndrome，即係頭痛出汗，皮膚發紅，呼吸困難咁。"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T22:42:21.000Z","msg":"有時出街食完 我都覺得有呢啲唔舒服！可能天生對味精比較敏感"},{"pid":"1f1cada9803e228c7f337f17c2245fecfc5fd8fd","tid":2348052,"uid":65289,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"e952d80b5bfa22f9070df20dd951bd264a1ab00b","tid":2348052,"uid":242909,"like":7,"dislike":1,"score":6,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T13:35:11.000Z","msg":"以為會有uncle roger<img src=\"/assets/faces/mousexm/potion.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T23:14:05.000Z","msg":"Your kid not smart, you put M S G"},{"pid":"5c3be84723feff82dad4c337dd89bfeb6e842210","tid":2348052,"uid":65289,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"027e1723029fd872c46451e843e77d5e27f1e355","tid":2348052,"uid":38121,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-12-31T22:09:19.000Z","msg":"MSG is considered safe by the FDA but has been blamed for headaches, flushing and difficulty breathing. <br />\n<br />\nContrary to popular belief, decades of research fails to support the link between MSG and these reported side effects.<br />\n<br />\nNo adverse symptoms were observed when people consumed MSG as part of a meal-even at high d